{"ID":270241, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"241\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs240.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs242.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 241<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">ance,<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> but when men have sinned, there must be allowance made for them.<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">All the religious world is boasting of righteousness; it is the doctrine of the devil to retard the\n  human mind,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> and hinder our progress, by filling us with self-righteousness. The nearer we get to\n  our heavenly Father, the more we are disposed to look with compassion on perishing souls;<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> we feel\n  that we want to take them upon our shoulders, and cast their sins behind our backs.<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> My talk is\n  intended for all this society; if you would have God have mercy on you,<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> have mercy on one\n  another.<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"wideEllipse\">* * *<\/p>\n\n  <div class=\"topic \">Men Cannot Be Compelled into Kingdom<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">He then made a promise in the name of the Lord, saying that that soul who has righteousness\n  enough to ask God in the secret place<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> for life, every day of their lives, shall live to three score years\n  and ten. We must walk uprightly<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> all the day long.<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> How glorious are the principles of\n  righteousness!<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> We are full of selfishness;<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> the devil flatters us<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> that we are very righteous, when\n  we are feeding on the faults of others.<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> We can only live by worshiping \n  our God;<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> all must do it for themselves; none can do it for another. How mild the Savior dealt with\n  Peter, saying, &ldquo;When thou art converted, strengthen thy brethren.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> At another time, He said to him,\n  &ldquo;Lovest thou me?&rdquo; and having received Peter&rsquo;s reply, He said, &ldquo;Feed my sheep.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> If the sisters\n  loved the Lord, let them feed the sheep,<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> and not destroy them.<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> How oft have wise men and\n  women sought to dictate Brother Joseph by saying, &ldquo;O, if I were Brother Joseph I would do this and\n  that;&rdquo; but if they were in Brother Joseph&rsquo;s shoes they would find that men or women could not be\n  compelled<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> into the kingdom of God, but must be dealt with in long-suffering,<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> and at last we shall\n  save them. The way to keep all the Saints together, and keep the work rolling, is to wait with all\n  long-suffering,<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> till God shall bring such characters to justice. There should be no license for sin,\n  but mercy should go hand in hand with reproof.<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Sisters of the society, shall there be strife among you?<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> I will not have it. You must repent, and\n  get the love of God.<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span> Away with self-righteousness!<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> The best measure or principle to bring the\n  poor to repentance is to administer to their wants.<span class=\"footRef\">27<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112336\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112336)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112336)\">Alma 45:16<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113077\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113077)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113077)\">D&amp;C 1:31<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111170\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111170)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111170)\">2 Ne. 9:7-10<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111436\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111436)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111436)\">Jacob 7:12<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111615\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111615)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111615)\">Mosiah 13:28<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112133\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112133)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112133)\">Alma 34:9-10<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110000\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110000)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110000)\">1 Tim. 3:6<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109242\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109242)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109242)\">Rom. 2:4<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109750\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109750)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109750)\">Gal. 6:1-2<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107164\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107164)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107164)\">Isa. 38:17<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107675\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107675)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"jav